abstract: If the protesters have not left by Aug. 27, the next step will be for a court bailiff to decide what, if any, action to take.
snippet: If the protesters have not left by Aug. 27, the next step will be for a court bailiff to decide what, if any, action to take.
lead_paragraph: HONG KONG — A Hong Kong judge on Monday gave a dwindling band of Occupy Hong Kong protesters two weeks to vacate the space below HSBC’s Asian headquarters, accepting a petition by the bank.

headline.main: Protesters In Hong Kong Ordered Out Of HSBC Site
headline.print_headline: Protesters In Hong Kong Ordered Out Of HSBC Site
